        <mxCell id="TysiPa89LfpG7-aD6HDz-51" value="• Retrenchment strategy is followed when an organization substantially reduces the&lt;br&gt;scope of its activity.&lt;br&gt;• Retrenchment strategy constitutes redefinition of business of the firm.&lt;br&gt;• A defensive strategy adopted as a temporary business policy to face problems like&lt;br&gt;intensive competition, lack of managerial abilities, change in market or economic&lt;br&gt;conditions.&lt;br&gt;• This involves reduction of products or services or withdrawal from some markets.&lt;br&gt;Retrenchment may be done either internally or externally.&lt;br&gt;• Internal Retrenchment is called as Turnaround Strategy; External Retrenchment is&lt;br&gt;called as Divestment. " style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="tAh5_Dv9XLEUhuwZVZgv-2">
